execute as @a[scores={HelpMessage=1}] at @s run tellraw @s ["",{"text":"\nThanks for installing the Paintifier Multiplayer Datapack!","bold":true,"color":"aqua"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"To get started, clear an area 16 blocks wide and 8 blocks tall and run one of the \"minecraft:paintifier_screens\" functions from a command block in the bottom left corner of the 16x8 area. This area is where the backlight for the screen will go, with the screen directly in front.","color":"aqua"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"The functions are named after the direction the screen will face when created. For example, if you want the screen to face east, you would run the \"minecraft:paintifier_screens/screen_face_east\" function from a command block.","color":"dark_aqua"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"To watch videos, install a resourcepack generated by the tool before joining the server and then join with the pack enabled. The sound will start automatically in sync with the video upon joining.","color":"blue"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"Note: Some syncing delay is expected. To fix any delay on the video, adjust the matching value inside jointimer.mcfunction located in \"functions/paintifier/jointimer.mcfunction\" on the last line of the file. By default, this value is 81. Setting this higher will make the sound start later, and setting it lower makes the sound start earlier. This value can be increased to a value up to 1000 ticks, or 50 seconds of delay.","bold":true,"color":"dark_blue"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"Click Here to join the Discord if you have any questions.","bold":true,"color":"light_purple","clickEvent":{"action":"open_url","value":"https://discord.gg/ESxRKUbe"}},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"Sorry for the extreme delay on this. Happy New Year, and happy video watching!","bold":true,"color":"black"},{"text":"\n"},{"text":"-thecolonel63","bold":true,"color":"black"}]
